<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="132" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[136,1452,158,724]" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,399,158,184]" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
—The species belongs to section 
<taxonomicName box="[772,834,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="27" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Sidae">
<emphasis box="[772,834,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">Sidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[849,931,158,184]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,340,364]" captionTargetBox="[144,1440,425,1289]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Sections of Sida with species occurring in Rio Grande do Sul state, and their diagnostic features, according to Fryxell (1985) and Krapovickas (2003)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39" pageId="27" pageNumber="132" tableUuid="539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39">Table 1</tableCitation>
) Series 
<emphasis box="[1024,1132,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">Viarumae</emphasis>
. This Series is characterized by the presence of 5 mericarps (
<bibRefCitation author="Krapovickas, A." box="[501,714,194,220]" pageId="27" pageNumber="132" pagination="65 - 118" refId="ref19583" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2014) Nuevas especies de Sida Seccion Sida (Malvaceae). Bonplandia 23: 65 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 232258" type="journal article" year="2014">Krapovickas 2014</bibRefCitation>
). The species is also characterized by the persistent stipules after leaf fall, by calyx 
<quantity box="[348,415,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="132" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long (
<bibRefCitation author="Monteiro-Filho, H. da" box="[490,731,230,256]" pageId="27" pageNumber="132" pagination="501 - 522" refId="ref20015" refString="Monteiro-Filho, H. da C. (1949) As especies argentinas, brasileiras e uruguayas da seccao Malvinda do genero Sida (Malvaceas). Lilloa 17: 501 - 522." type="journal article" year="1949">Monteiro-Filho 1949</bibRefCitation>
) and corolla white with adaxial red basal spot (
<figureCitation box="[1281,1447,230,256]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="23.[136,229,1993,2015]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,190,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-17@23.[164,1423,190,1968]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 12. A–E. Sida urens. A. Flower. B. Adaxial surface of leaf. C. Branch with flowers and flowers buds. D. Schizocarp. E. Branch with mature schizocarps. F–J. Sida viarum. F. Flower. G. Adaxial surface of leaf. H. Abaxial surface of leaf. I. Branch. J. Immature schizocarps and leaves. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415513/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">Figures 12F–J</figureCitation>
, 
