<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="132" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="27.[136,1452,158,724]" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,738,302,328]" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[766,903,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="27" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viarum">
<emphasis box="[766,903,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">Sida viarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a South American species (
<collectingCountry box="[1247,1363,302,328]" name="Argentina" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1376,1447,302,328]" name="Brazil" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[136,218,338,364]" name="Bolivia" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[279,385,339,365]" name="Paraguay" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
) that reaches as far north, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[806,892,338,364]" name="Mexico" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fryxell, P. A." box="[910,1062,338,364]" pageId="27" pageNumber="132" pagination="1 - 522" refId="ref18772" refString="Fryxell, P. A. (1988) Malvaceae of Mexico. Systematic Botany Monograph 25: 1 - 522. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 25027717" type="journal article" year="1988">Fryxell 1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J." box="[1076,1306,338,364]" pageId="27" pageNumber="132" pagination="1 - 3348" refId="ref20813" refString="Zuloaga, F. O., Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J. (2008) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur (Argentina, sur de Brasil, Chile, Paraguay y Uruguay). Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 107: 1 - 3348." type="journal article" year="2008">
Zuloaga 
<emphasis box="[1178,1237,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alverson, W. S. &amp; Michel, L. R. C. de &amp; Dorr, L. J. &amp; Fryxell, P. A. &amp; Krapovickas, A. &amp; Meneses, Q. R. I." pageId="27" pageNumber="132" pagination="786 - 819" refId="ref17710" refString="Alverson, W. S., Michel, L. R. C. de, Dorr, L. J., Fryxell, P. A., Krapovickas, A. &amp; Meneses, Q. R. I. (2014) Malvaceae. In: Jorgensen, P. M., Nee, M. H. &amp; Beck, S. G. (Eds.) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares de Bolivia, Monographs in systematic botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden. Missouri Botanical Garden Press., St. Louis, pp. 786 - 819." type="book chapter" year="2014">
Alverson 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[287,355,374,400]" name="Brazil" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">Brazil</collectingCountry>
the species occurs in north, northeast, midwest, southeast and south region, but not in all states (
<bibRefCitation author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J." box="[144,362,410,436]" pageId="27" pageNumber="132" pagination="1 - 3348" refId="ref20813" refString="Zuloaga, F. O., Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J. (2008) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur (Argentina, sur de Brasil, Chile, Paraguay y Uruguay). Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 107: 1 - 3348." type="journal article" year="2008">
Zuloaga 
<emphasis box="[243,298,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bovini, M. G." box="[372,515,410,436]" pageId="27" pageNumber="132" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In Rio Grande Sul, the species is distributed in Bush grassland, Inland sub-montane grassland, Sandy grassland, Coastal grassland, and occasionally in 
<taxonomicName box="[887,977,446,472]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Aristida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="27" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Aristida</taxonomicName>
grassland (
<figureCitation box="[1105,1218,446,472]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[266,1345,253,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-25@24.[204,1384,190,1933]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distribution map of Sida urens and S. viarum in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415517/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="132">Figure 13</figureCitation>
). The species is here considered Least Concern (LC) because it has a large EOO (greater than 
<quantity box="[969,1127,482,511]" metricMagnitude="9" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="132" unit="km" value="3000000.0">3,000,000 km</quantity>
²) and an AOO around 2,000 with the available records.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
